headline: GE Vernova Growth Supercycle Tied To AI Power And Payouts
summary: GE Vernova (NYSE:GEV) is reporting a growth supercycle supported by strong demand from AI data centers and wider power needs. The company cites large order intake and a substantial contract backlog as key drivers of its current momentum. Management has doubled the dividend and expanded the share buyback program as part of a broader capital return plan. For investors watching NYSE:GEV, the story now centers on how its power solutions are tied into the build out of AI and digital...
